         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/7/92 ¶  ¶ I am very grateful to you, dear Mr Tyson, for the specimens of plants, just received from you. Probably your kind brothers helped collecting. I will write at once to the firms, mentioned ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.07.28a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Isaac Tyson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 58 (044) MUE, WA Herbarium, Perth.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/7/92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am very grateful to you, dear Mr Tyson, for the specimens of plants, just received from you. Probably your kind brothers helped collecting. I will write at once to the firms, mentioned by you. More postage stamps can be sent from time to time. As you ask, let me say that I like specimens in fruit (ripe) of all your Mulga-<name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s and indeed of any other kinds of <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s growing near you, as these will aid me in finishing my large illustrated work on the Australian <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would not encourage you to grow any <name key="Lathyrus">Lathyrus</name> for fodder, as they are apt, when much fed on, to cause paralysis. I sent Mr Dale in Perth lately roots of the "wonder-grass" <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name>. If he succeeds in growing this marvellous pasture-grass, you might ask him for some rooted offshoots.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lathyrus">Lathyrus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name>
            </p>
         </div>
